  "prompt": "What celebrities have converted to Islam?",
  "response": "Several celebrities have publicly converted to Islam over the years. Here are some notable examples:\n\n1. **Muhammad Ali** - The legendary boxer converted to Islam in 1964, changing his name from Cassius Clay. He became one of the most famous Muslim figures globally and was known for his activism and faith.\n\n2. **Janet Jackson** - The singer and actress reportedly converted to Islam in the early 2010s after marrying Qatari businessman Wissam Al Mana.\n\n3. **Mike Tyson** - The former heavyweight boxing champion converted to Islam while serving a prison sentence in the 1990s.\n\n4. **Busta Rhymes** - The rapper announced his conversion to Islam in 2021, stating that it brought him peace and clarity.\n\n5. **Jermaine Jackson** - A member of the Jackson 5 and older brother of Michael Jackson, Jermaine converted to Islam in the 1980s.\n\n6. **French Montana** - The rapper, born Karim Kharbouch, is a practicing Muslim and often discusses his faith publicly.\n\n7. **Dave Chappelle** - The comedian converted to Islam in the late 1990s, though he has kept his faith relatively private.\n\n8. **Shabba Ranks** - The Jamaican dancehall artist converted to Islam in the 1990s.\n\n9. **Yusuf Islam (formerly Cat Stevens)** - The British singer-songwriter converted to Islam in 1977 and changed his name. He is now known for his philanthropic work and devotion to his faith.\n\n10. **Akon** - The Senegalese-American singer and producer, born Aliaune Thiam, is a practicing Muslim and often incorporates his faith into his work.\n\n11. **DJ Khaled** - The music producer and DJ is a devout Muslim and frequently references his faith in his music and public appearances.\n\n12. **Everlast** - The rapper and singer, best known for his hit \"What It's Like,\" converted to Islam in the early 2000s.\n\nThese celebrities have shared their journeys to Islam, often citing spiritual growth, peace, and personal transformation as reasons for their conversion.",
